PWR reactors are the backbone of modern nuclear, and companies like NuScale proved how far a compact PWR design can go with full NRC certification. Hadron Energy is taking that same proven foundation and pushing it into the next era. 

Smaller footprints, faster deployment, and higher resilience for defense and commercial use.

A PWR-based microreactor gives you what the market wants right now — water-cooled, highly stable, familiar to regulators, and already trusted by the nuclear industry.




NuScale’s $SMR technology is compatible with advanced fuels, keeping this sustainable option open for the future.

Responsible waste management is a cornerstone of sustainable nuclear energy. The methods used are not new or experimental. They are proven, regulated, and safe.




NuScale Power Modules (NPMs) can ramp their power output up or down depending on how much renewable energy (like wind or solar) is available at any given moment.





The NuScale/ORNL TEA study doesn’t list specific chemicals by name, but it focuses on chemical plants that require large amounts of process steam and electricity. In practice, this generally applies to industries like:
    •    Petrochemicals & refining – e.g., production of ethylene, propylene, ammonia, and other hydrocarbon derivatives.
    •    Fertilizers – especially ammonia (NH₃) and urea plants, which require high-temperature steam for synthesis.
    •    Industrial gases & basic chemicals – hydrogen, methanol, chlorine, caustic soda.
    •    Specialty chemicals & polymers – plastics, resins, and other high-volume industrial chemicals that need heat and electricity.

The key point is any plant that relies on high-temperature process steam (~400°C / 752°F) and substantial electrical power could integrate NuScale SMRs profitably.




Ammonia is essential to global food security — and today it’s also one of the most carbon-intensive chemicals produced. The reason isn’t chemistry, it’s energy. 

Nearly all ammonia emissions come from fossil-based hydrogen production. By coupling proven electrolyzers with reliable nuclear power from SMRs like NuScale’s, ammonia production can be fully electrified, 
continuously operated, and scaled without massive storage or intermittency risk.
For industrial commodities, reliability and utilization matter — and that’s where nuclear quietly outperforms.





